AB  - This paper applies the waiting-time regression methods of Olsen and Wolpin (1983) to an analysis of fertility. A utility-maximizing model is set up and used to provide some guidance for an empirical analysis. Data are from an experimental guaranteed job program, the Youth Incentive Entitlement Pilot Project. The study finds that young women consider the economic consequences of fertility.
